    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Language family of central Eurasia and Siberia, now believed by some to be a sprachbund rather than a family; a sprachbund would be a group of languages that have common features resulting from geographical proximity and language contact, but not necessarily otherwise related.</Note_Text>
